main event: Multiple unidentified bright objects were reported in Alaska from January 25 to January 29, 1965, appearing as star-like bodies.
interesting points: Reports included bright lights observed over various locations, witnesses believed these objects to be very close, some described them as resembling searchlights, the sightings caused considerable public interest and reaction, and a mix of civilian and military personnel were involved in the observations.
witness description: civilian residents, housewives, policemen, and chemistry students
